sec.p:
Nozzle is designed according to the assumption of fully expanded flow. The mass flow and regulator outlet pressure will confine the throat area. The nozzle total inlet pressure to exit pressure will determine the exit Mach number and finally Mach number and the amount of thrust will provide the exit diameter. The profile of the nozzle is depended on:


– efficiency of the nozzle profile which is related to the axial flow with the minimum loss;

– the complexity of profile which determines the cost of manufacturing production;

– the magnitude of base drag;

– nozzle weight and size.

As aforementioned, the components of cold gas propulsion system may have restrictions on temperature and pressure which limit the design process. It should be noticed that these restrictions should not be discarded. Since the temperature and pressure limits cannot be satisfied simultaneously, the amount of the residual mass of the fluid can increase to satisfy these restrictions. The system of ODEs will be solved repetitively to obtain the most reasonable result. As the design parameters change, the size and the weight of the components and thereupon system gross weight will change subsequently. The three criterions which assist us to choose the most satisfactory values are as follows:


– minimum net weight;

– the minimum volume for the system;

– the best performance of the system.
